'''bTV Radio''' is a Bulgarian [[radio station]], part of bTV Radio Group, owned by the Central European Media Enterprises(owned by [[WarnerMedia]]/[[AT&T]]). It broadcasts from May 1, 2009 in [[Sofia]], and later launched in [[Pernik]] and [[Gotse Delchev]]. Its program is also transmitted via satellite across Europe. The station originally launched as a radio program of the television [[PRO.BG]] - PRO.FM. From October 2011, it is re-branded to the eponymous radio station of the television channel [[bTV (Bulgaria)|bTV]], emitting the main of the television program. The radio will go on broadcasting only in Sofia.

