'''''Keltainen Pörssi''''' ([[Finnish language|Finnish]] for "the yellow stock market") was [[Finland]]'s most popular small ads magazine. The magazine was established in 1986<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.keltainenporssi.fi/contact/|work=Yhteystiedot|date=21 July 2012|title=Contact}}</ref> and is part of [[Sanoma]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SanomaWSOY's Interim Report 1 January - 30 June 2005|url=http://sanoma.com/en/news/sanomawsoys-interim-report-1-january-30-june-2005-0|work=Sanoma|accessdate=25 October 2015|date=4 January 2005}}</ref> Ilta-Sanomat Oy was the publisher of the magazine of which the headquarters was in [[Helsinki]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Keltainen Pörssi|url=http://www.publicitas.com/en/canada/media-solutions/factsheet/mediadata/keltainenporssifi-website/?PARAM1=SHLHH8#.VixuW2ThB1M|publisher=Publicitas|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref name="san6">{{cite news|title=Autot - a New Keltainen Pörssi Theme Publication|url=https://sanoma.com/en/news/autot-new-keltainen-porssi-theme-publication|accessdate=29 December 2016|work=Sanoma|date=17 March 2006}}</ref>

It was available both as a print edition published twice per week and a free online edition, and consisted entirely of small ads by private citizens. These ads were divided into categories for easy browsing. Placing an ad was free of charge, but extra stand-out features and [[photograph]]s costed money.

''Keltainen Pörssi'' had several [[supplement (publishing)|supplement]]s, including ''Autot''.<ref name="san6"/>

In 2016 the publication was wound down and visits to the web address directed users to the [[Huuto.net]] site, this is a online ''auction'' and ''buy it now''  site similar to eBay that caters for the Finnish market.  Keltainen Pörssi was owned by the same media group with Huuto.net and [[Ilta-Sanomat]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hujanen|first1=Miikka|title=Keltainen Pörssi lopettaa – palstalla ostettiin salmiakkikossua, merikarhu etsi naisseuraa...|url=http://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000001208957.html|accessdate=5 June 2017|date=2016-06-27}}</ref>

