{{refimprove|date=January 2014}}
The '''Microfinance Investment Support Facility for Afghanistan (MISFA)''' was set up in 2003 at the invitation of the [[government of Afghanistan|Afghan government]] to streamline collection of [[charitable donation|donor money]] and avoid pitfalls arising from conflicting donor interests that had been seen in other post-conflict situations. It was established as a vehicle through which the [[Afghanistan|Afghan]] government and international donors could channel technical assistance and funding to build Afghanistan’s [[microfinance]] sector.
In March 2006, MISFA registered as a [[limited liability company|limited liability]], [[non-profit company]] whose sole shareholder is the [[Ministry of Finance (Afghanistan)|Ministry of Finance of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan]]. MISFA Ltd is an independent apex organization with a number of implementing partners on the ground. In most cases, MISFA functions as either the exclusive or primary provider of funds to its partners. The legal status of MFIs has been transformed from [[NGO]]s to that of non-profit companies registered with the [[Afghanistan Investment Support Agency]] (AISA), as permanent institutions under the [[law of Afghanistan]].
==Related external links== * [http://www.misfa.org.af/ '''Microfinance Investment Support Facility for Afghanistan (MISFA)''' website] * [http://www.ama.org.af/ Afghanistan Microfinance Association (AMA)] * [https://t-o-i.org// Tikkun Olam Micro-Finance (T-O-M)]
