{{Infobox Union |name= Norwegian Union of Railway Workers |country= [[Norway]] |affiliation= [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions|LO]] |members= |full_name= |native_name= Norsk Jernbaneforbund |image= [[File:NJF logo.png]] |founded= 20 November 1892 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Oslo]], Norway |people= |website= [http://www.njf.no www.njf.no] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Norwegian Union of Railway Workers''' ({{lang-no|Norsk Jernbaneforbund}}, NJF) is a [[trade union]] in [[Norway]]. It was formed on 20 November 1892, and mainly organizes workers in [[Norwegian State Railways|Norges Statsbaner]]&mdash;with the exception of locomotive drivers&mdash; and the [[Norwegian National Rail Administration]], including related companies such as [[BaneTele]], [[Nettbuss]], [[Nettlast]], [[Malmtrafik]], [[MiTrans]], [[Mantena]], [[Trafikkservice]], [[CargoNet]], [[Baneservice]], [[Arrive (company)|Arrive]], [[Ofotbanen (company)|Ofotbanen AS]], [[NSB Gjøvikbanen]] and [[Flytoget]].<ref name=about>[http://njf.no/organisasjon/ About the Norwegian Union of Railway Workers]</ref>
It is affiliated with the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]] (LO), and is a member of the [[International Transport Workers' Federation]].<ref name=about/>
Former leaders include [[Ludvik Buland]] and [[John Marius Trana]].<ref>[http://njf.no/organisasjon/historikk History of the Norwegian Union of Railway Workers] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090120202953/http://njf.no/organisasjon/historikk |date=2009-01-20 }}</ref>
