{{Infobox political party | name = Parochial Union of Independents Group | logo = [[Image:Gupielectionsymbol.jpg|GUPi symbol]] | colorcode = Purple | ideology =[[Progressivism]] | headquarters = [[Ordino]] | country = Andorra }}
The '''Parochial Union of Independents Group''' ({{lang-ca|Grup d'Unió Parroquial Independents}}, GUPI) is a local [[progressivism|progressive]] [[political party]] in [[Ordino]], [[Andorra]].
==History== In the local elections in 2003 GUPI won two of the ten seats in Ordino. For the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2005|2005 parliamentary elections]] the party was part of an alliance with the [[Social Democratic Party (Andorra)|Social Democratic Party]] and [[Democratic Renewal (Andorra)|Democratic Renewal]] named '''L'Alternativa'''.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen D]] & Stöver P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p164 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The alliance won twelve seats.
GUPI retained its alliance with the Social Democratic Party for the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2009|2009 elections]], with the coalition emerging victorious after winning 14 of the 28 seats.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/2005_09.htm Elections in 2009] IPU</ref>
