{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Bethlehem |latin = Dioecesis Bethlehemensis |country = {{flag|South Africa}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bloemfontein|Bloemfontein]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |area_km2 = 34,965 |population = 946,000 |population_as_of = 2006 |catholics = 77,600 |catholics_percent= 8.2 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Jan de Groef]], [[White Fathers|M. Afr.]] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Bethlehem''' ({{lang-la|Bethlehemen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Bethlehem, Free State|Bethlehem]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bloemfontein|Bloemfontein]] in [[South Africa]].
==History== * February 12, 1948: Established as Apostolic Vicariate of Bethlehem from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Kroonstad]] * January 11, 1951: Promoted as Diocese of Bethlehem
==Special churches== The [[Cathedral]] is the Cathedral of the Immaculate Heart of Mary in Bethlehem.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Bethlehem (Roman rite) ** Bishop [[Jan de Groef]], [[White Fathers|M. Afr.]] (since 2008.12.31) ** Bishop [[Hubert Bucher]] (1976.12.09 - 2008.12.31) ** Bishop [[Peter Kelleter]], [[C.S.Sp.]] (1951.01.11 – 1975.07.05) * Vicars Apostolic of Bethlehem (Roman rite) ** Bishop Peter Kelleter, C.S.Sp. (1950.03.12 – 1951.01.11) ** Bishop [[Léon Klerlein]], C.S.Sp. (1948.02.12 – 1950.05.22)
